      <mj-spacer height="14px" />
          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Putting ‘service’ in the driver’s seat</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          Peter Lewis transformed Progressive from the nation’s 48th-largest auto insurer into a leading competitor. One of his most groundbreaking moves was redefining customer service in an industry notorious for avoiding payouts. His philosophy was simple: since consumers generally disliked their insurers, <strong>exceptional service and accessibility would set Progressive apart</strong>.
         </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">In 1990, Progressive introduced a <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-08-02-2025-3-24-7-immediate-response-claims?source=website" target="_blank">24/7 immediate response claims</a> service. By 1994, it revolutionized the industry with Immediate Response Vehicles, providing on-the-spot assistance to policyholders. That same year, it <strong>launched the first toll-free, 24/7 auto insurance comparison service</strong>. A simple call to 1-800-AUTO-PRO gave customers a "Progressive Quote" alongside rates from three top insurers.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>In 1995, they launched auto-insurance.com (later renamed Progressive.com)</strong>, becoming the first major insurer to offer online quotes. This approach gave the company a significant competitive edge. Instead of treating insurance as another financial product, Lewis positioned it as a service-centered industry. </p>
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Peter Lewis takes the fast lane</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Lewis spent a decade researching and experimenting before Progressive introduced a product model that rated all auto owners and operators in standard and non-standard markets. Progressive was among the first insurers to <strong>integrate consumer credit histories and telematics data into pricing models</strong>, allowing for more personalized and accurate policy premiums.</p>
          </mj-text>

          <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px 14px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/peter-lewis-takes-the-fast-lane.png?source=website" alt="Peter B. Lewis in 2001, a year after he provided a smooth transition to his successor" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />
           <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            Peter B. Lewis in 2001, a year after he engineered a smooth transition to his successor at Progressive Corp. Credits: Cleveland.com
          </p>
        </mj-text>

          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Lewis saw beyond auto insurance, recognizing a broader role for Progressive in the motor. In 1999, Progressive became the first insurer to offer instant online quotes for motorcycles, boats, and watercraft. <strong>Over time, it evolved into Progressive Corporation, a diversified insurance holding company</strong> covering personal, commercial, and specialty property insurance. Its offerings expanded to include coverage for RVs, ATVs, snowmobiles, and various commercial vehicles, from small business trucks to taxis, tow trucks, and long-haul rigs.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">In 2012, a year before his passing, Lewis was named one of the 25 “<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-08-02-2025-4-living-legends-of-insurance?source=website" target="_blank">Living Legends of Insurance</a>” by National Underwriter Property & Casualty. He built Progressive into the <strong>fourth-largest auto insurer in the US</strong>, insuring 10 million policyholders. Additionally, he made himself into one of the nation’s leading philanthropists. He supported the arts, education, politics, and marijuana legalization.</p>
          </mj-text> 
      </mj-column>
